@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Dead Letter Queue

' When a job cannot be processed it must not be silently dropped
' or left to block the topic. It goes to a DLQ, where you can inspect it and
' replay it later, for example once a dependency the worker needs is back up.

skinparam shadowing false

queue "job.requests" as reqs
participant "python-worker" as worker
database "Postgres" as pg
queue "job.requests.dlq\n(dead-letter)" as dlq

reqs -> worker : consume { jobId, payload, owner }

alt success
  worker -> pg : UPDATE row -> 'completed'
else failure (bad message, or a dependency down)
  worker -> pg : UPDATE row -> 'failed' (best effort)
  worker -> dlq : produce { original, reason, error }
end

note over worker : Retry transient errors first. Send to the DLQ once retries are exhausted.

note over dlq
  Nothing is lost and the topic is not blocked.
  Transient when a dependency was down, so replay when it is back.
  Poison when permanently bad, so fix it then replay. Alert on depth.
end note

dlq --> reqs : replay (re-publish) when healthy

@enduml
